\b MOUSE CLICK OPTIONS
\f3\b0\fs18 \

\f0\fs24 \

\b Clicking on a URL Link Works Only If It Is Underlined
\b0  - If this is enabled, you can only click on an \ul underlined\ulnone  web address URL or email address to launch your web browser or email program. If this option is disabled, It will launch the app even if the address is not underlined.\
For host controlled browser launching that does not require clicking, see\
"Launching Your Browser and Sending Email Under Host Control"\
\

\b Send Carriage Return on Single Mouse Click
\b0  - When you click on a menu number or word in the MacWise window, it will be sent to the host and a carriage return will be sent. Otherwise, just the number or word is sent and no carriage return.\
\pard\ql\qnatural
\cf0 \
\pard\li360\ri360\ql\qnatural

\b \cf0 Mouse Click Delimiter Character
\f2  - 
\f0\b0  The Mouse Clicks button Lets you specify the character that immediately follows your host menu item numbers (usually a period). This allows you to click on a menu item number without sending the period (or whatever character you specify). Also, If you click on any word on the screen, it will be sent to the host.\
\

\b Mouse Click Sends Column,row to host
\b0 \
\pard\li360\ri-1380\ql\qnatural
\cf0 Mouse click sends its cursor position to host preceded by ESC MOUSE\
(CCC,RR  where C=Column and R=Row)\
Example:\
Mouse is clicked on column 5 row 20\
MacWise sends ESC MOUSE 005,20 CR\
(where ESC = ASCII decimal 27 and CR = ASCII decimal 13)\
NOTE: Rows start at row zero for this function.
\f1\fs26 \

\f0\fs24 \
\pard\li360\ri360\ql\qnatural

\b \cf0 Click on System Builder Menus
\b0  - When communicating with host computers running System Builder software, this option lets you click on menu items within the window to select the menu item.\
\

\b Disable Mouse Clicks
\b0  - When you click the mouse on text in the MacWise window, nothing will happen if this option is enabled. However, you can still click on the fkey buttons at the bottom of the window.\
\
