\b \cf0 More Preferences Information
\b0 \
Versions of MacWise prior to version 10.b3 stored the settings in the MacWise folder.\
Settings are now stored in the user's Preference folder.\
This was done to accomodate multiple users on one Mac.\
You can log in with a different user name and your settings can be personalized.\
The MacWise folder is still shared among users. It is in the Applications folder.\
\
To find the MacWise preferences folder:\
Open your hard drive and click on the Home icon.\
Open the Library folder\
Open the Preferences folder\
Open the Carnation Software Prefs folder\
Open the 
\f4 MacWise Prefs folder\
Now you will see at least four files that belong to MacWise:\
defaults - stores most of your settings\
fkeydefaults - stores your fkey settings\
QuickDial - stores your QuickDial number for dialing with the modem.\
Recorder - the default file to hold data you record with the capture menu.
